-Updated HTSD website with our new logo & color palette.

post_text:
Northstar Alum shines brightly in DIVOS!

Nottingham High School Northstar Alum, Matt Steele, wrote and stars in the feature film DIVOS! Available beginning today via all major Video On Demand services, including iTunes, Amazon, YouTube Movies & Shows, Google Play, XBox, Vudu, and more. (See divosthemovie.com for a full listing of services.)

Matt is a proud alumni of Nottingham High School, Crockett Middle School, and Mercerville Elementary school. He graduated from NYU in 2010 and spent his college years writing comedic plays that were performed at Nottingham High School. He moved to Los Angeles a few years ago to pursue a career in film. DIVOS! is the first feature film he wrote.

Isaac Gonzalez (a recent graduate of Hamilton High West) can also be seen in a small role in the film.

As events surrounding COVID 19 (Coronavirus) continue to unfold rapidly, it is essential that we are fully prepared as a district for the possibility of remote learning for students. With this in mind, the Hamilton Township School District will run on a one session day tomorrow, Friday, March 13th for our students to allow faculty and staff to continue their preparation in the afternoon.

Thank you in advance for your cooperation and continued support.

Hamilton Township School District - Mercer County added 21 new photos.
February 7 at 4:39 PM ·

Kisthardt Elementary School celebrated World Read Aloud Day by having students read to each other in the classroom as well as two school wide presentations. The first presentation featured Kisthardt principal Debbie Glomb reading aloud to Luna, a local therapy dog who often comes to Kisthardt to help students feel more comfortable reading aloud. The second presentation featured Natalie Megules, an opera singer and actress, who read and acted out three stories for the Kisthardt students. Great job, Kisthardt, and keep reading!
